															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/smapti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(362048); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=362048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250869" alt="Smapti" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=362048)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/smapti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(362048); return false;" >Smapti</a></span> <span class="odate time_1338669062 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Jun 2012 20:31</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1468631">
									

<p>It's in keeping with how he's addressed in the original article's interview log. That article doesn't even name him SCP-662-1 at all, probably because it's an older one and that usage hadn't been standardized yet at the time. I created that designation for this tale because just calling him Mr. Deeds in the intro felt inappropriate, but it works in the log himself since we want Deeds to cooperate and calling him that seems to make him comfortable.</p>
<p>(If we want to <em>really</em> get picky, convention would dictate that a valet be addressed simply by his last name without the courtesy title, so he should be &quot;Deeds&quot; and not &quot;Mr. Deeds&quot;, but i'm not going to go rewriting someone else's SCP for the purposes of my tale.)</p>

							</div>

								
